Business Brief -- Carolco Pictures Inc.:
   Work Force to Be Cut 13%
   As Part of Restructuring
The company is in the midst of a bailout by its foreign
partners, which include Pioneer Electronic Corp. of Japan; a
unit of Canal S.A. of France; and RCS Video International
Services B.V., an affiliate of Rizzoli Corriere della Sera
Group. Last week, Carolco completed a tender offer to redeem
$67.4 million of its 14% senior notes.